public class Factorial {

   // method to compute the factorial
    static int factorial(int n){      
          if (n <= 1)      
            return 1;      
          else      
            return(n * factorial(n-1));      
    }      
  
    public static void main(String[] args) {  
      logical_step_1: Declare an integer variable n and  assign to it a value of 3.
      logical_step_details: Declare an integer variable of value 3 
      question_1: What does the block of code do?
      answer_1: it computes the factorial of 3 and print it.
      question_1: How the factorial of 3 is computed?
      answer_1: factorial(3)=3*factorial(2)=3*2*factorial(1)= 3*2*1
      int n = 3
      System.out.println("Factorial of n is: "+factorial(n));  
  }  
}  
